  "question": "In a dance class of 20 students, 20% enrolled in contemporary dance, 25% of the remaining enrolled in jazz dance, and the rest enrolled in hip-hop dance. What percentage of the entire students enrolled in hip-hop dance?",
  "prompt": "In a dance class of 20 students, 20% enrolled in contemporary dance, 25% of the remaining enrolled in jazz dance, and the rest enrolled in hip-hop dance. What percentage of the entire students enrolled in hip-hop dance?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "60",
  "generated_text": "To find the percentage of students enrolled in hip-hop dance, we can break down the enrollment process step by step.\n\n**Step 1: Calculate the number of students in contemporary dance.**\nThe total number of students is 20.\n20% of the total students are in contemporary dance.\n$$ \\text{Contemporary} = 20\\% \\times 20 = 0.20 \\times 20 = 4 \\text{ students} $$\n\n**Step 2: Calculate the number of remaining students after contemporary dance.**\nSubtract the contemporary dancers from the total.\n$$ \\text{Remaining} = 20 - 4 = 16 \\text{ students} $$\n\n**Step 3: Calculate the number of students in jazz dance.**\n25% of the *remaining* students (16) are in jazz dance.\n$$ \\text{Jazz} = 25\\% \\times 16 = 0.25 \\times 16 = 4 \\text{ students} $$\n\n**Step 4: Calculate the number of students in hip-hop dance.**\nThe rest of the students enroll in hip-hop dance. First, find the number of remaining students after jazz dance:\n$$ \\text{Remaining after Jazz} = 16 - 4 = 12 \\text{ students} $$\nAlternatively, you can calculate the hip-hop percentage directly:\n$$ \\text{Hip-hop \\%} = 100\\% - (\\text{Contemporary \\%} + \\text{Jazz \\%}) = 100\\% - (20\\% + 25\\%) = 100\\% - 45\\% = 55\\% $$\nNow apply this to the total count:\n$$ \\text{Hip-hop count} = 55\\% \\times 20 = 0.55 \\times 20 = 11 \\text{ students} $$\n\n**Step 5: Calculate the percentage of the entire class.**\nThe question asks for the percentage of the *entire* students enrolled in hip-hop.\n$$ \\text{Percentage} = \\frac{\\text{Hip-hop count}}{\\text{Total count}} \\times 100\\% $$\n$$ \\text{Percentage} = \\frac{11}{20} \\times 100\\% = 0.55 \\times 100\\% = 55\\% $$\n\nAlternatively, using the direct percentage calculation from Step 4:\nSince the hip-hop percentage is 55% of the total class, the answer is simply 55%.\n\n\\boxed{55\\%}\n",
